location.fullValue: Starling Plan, Sanctuary Cove at Cane Bay

data.description: Sellers are offering $5k towards closing cost and a 13 month home warranty to buyer.  This beautifully appointed home has 3 beds/2.5 bath located in one of the most desirable locations within Cane Bay, this home offers unparalleled charm. Tucked away in a serene cul-de-sac, it is embraced by a wooded park space at your doorstep and a picturesque pond to enjoy from the comfort of your screen porch. Nestled near the front of the development, you'll relish swift access to all the splendid offerings of Cane Bay. The convenience is ideal - children can easily stroll to school, while an array of shops and amenities are mere moments away. The main level unveils an open concept layout, creating an irresistibly cozy and welcoming ambiance for cherished family moments and social gatheringa great office or an additional bedroom complete with its own closet. The kitchen seamlessly flows into the dining area and family room, showcasing stainless steel appliances and a fantastic gas range - a true delight for the family's chef. The kitchen host bar top for additional seating for casual dining. Venturing upstairs, a generously proportioned loft area beckons for relaxation. The master bedroom is a serene retreat, featuring tranquil pond vistas, a separate shower and tub, and an expansive walk-in closet. Adjacent to the loft, you'll find the secondary bedrooms, a second full bathroom, and a laundry room, all boasting walk-in closets for added storage convenience. Step outside to the charming screened-in porch and relish in the beauty of nature with calming pond views. The two-car garage adds a touch of practicality to this already exceptional property. Don't miss this one, schedule your showing today.  As the day winds down, you can embrace the natural beauty of South Carolina right from your own backyard. Step onto your private screened-in back porch and take in the serene views of one of the tranquil ponds that grace the neighborhood.  Cane Bay community is filled with neighborhoods built by well-respected builders, great schools, shopping, healthcare, recreation, and waterfront properties with exclusive access to an expansive lake system, all connected by miles of meandering trails. It's no wonder Cane Bay has been the top-selling community in South Carolina for years.   Lowcountry Living in Berkeley County not only offers the lowest millage rate for taxes in the tri-county area but there is a value to the quality lifestyle you will enjoy. Berkeley County is known for its natural beauty and historic landmarks including historic Jamestown, serene Mepkin Abbey, lush Cypress Gardens and the impressive Beidler Forest. In addition, this county offers more water for recreation than any place in the state, including Lake Moultrie, Lake Marion, and the Cooper and Santee Rivers known for their world-class fishing. And the Francis Marion National Forest holds 250,000 acres of diverse plant and animal life with biking, hiking and horseback trails for exploring.  Easy Access to schools, shops and restaurants!
